    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "PIA Passenger Timetable\nPakistan International Airlines\nWinter 1968-69\nEffective Nov. 1, 1968\nMember of IATA",
      "The Other Side of the World.\nThis is the land of man's beginning.\nThe land of the first wheel. The first writ-\nten word.\nWhere Pharoahs ruled. Where Alexander\ncarved out an Empire.\nWhere mosques and minarets and mar-\nket places still echo the voice of history.\nWhere legend lives in the Khyber Pass.\nThe streets of Baghdad. And the ruins of\nPersepolis.\nThis is The Other Side of the World.\nAnd this is where PIA flies.\nEvery day of the week. (Eleven times\nweekly\nfrom\nLondon.\nAnd\nfrom\nParis,\nGeneva, Rome, Frankfurt and Moscow.)\nStep aboard one of our Boeing 707's and\nwe'll take you on a flight to antiquity. In\ntraditional Pakistani hospitality.\nPakistan International Airlines.\nThe on-time airline to The Other Side of\nthe World."
    ],
